===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|sisours}}, {{m|enm|sisoures}} (attested since 1350–1400), from {{der|en|fro|cisoires}}, from {{etyl|VL.|en}} {{m|la|*cīsōria}}, plural of {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|cīsōrium||cutting tool}} (compare {{m|en|chisel}}); from {{etyl|la|en}} word root {{m|la||-cīsus}} (compare {{m|en|excise}}) or {{m|la|caesus}}, past participle of {{m|la|caedō||to cut}}.
* The current spelling, from the 16th century, is due to association with {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la||scissor|tailor}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} carrying the meaning “carver, cutter”, from {{m|la|scindo|scindere|to split}}.

