===Noun===
{{en-noun|scissors}}

# {{lb|en|countable|usually|construed as plural}} A [[tool]] used for [[cut]]ting thin material, consisting of two crossing blades attached at a [[pivot]] point in such a way that the blades slide across each other when the handles are closed.
#: {{ux|en|Those '''scissors''' are sharp.}} (indicating singular or plural scissors)
#: {{ux|en|That '''scissors''' is sharp.}} (less commonly to indicate singular scissors)
#: {{ux|en|'''Scissors''' are used to cut the flowers.}}
#: {{ux|en|Use '''scissors''' to cut them if you don't have proper shears.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|title=Around the Garden|work=New York Times|date=Jun 22, 1947|passage=Roses will last longer if a knife rather than a '''scissors''' is used to cut the blooms.}}
# {{lb|en|countable|rugby}} An attacking move conducted by two players; the player without the ball runs from one side of the [[ball carrier]], behind the ball carrier, and receives a [[pass]] from the ball carrier on the other side.
#: {{ux|en|They executed a perfect '''scissors'''.}}
# {{lb|en|countable|skating}} A method of skating with one foot significantly in front of the other.
# {{lb|en|countable|gymnastics}} An exercise in which the legs are switched back and forth, suggesting the motion of scissors.
# {{lb|en|countable|wrestling}} A [[scissors hold]].
# {{lb|en|[[rock paper scissors]]}} A [[hand]] with the [[index finger|index]] and [[middle finger|middle]] fingers open (a [[handshape]] resembling scissors), that beats [[paper]] and is loses to [[rock]]. It beats [[lizard]] and loses to [[Spock]] in [[rock-paper-scissors-lizard-Spock]].

